The Economic Freedom Fighters have called for this year's local government elections to be put on the back-burner. The party wants them postponed to 2024. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Economic Freedom Fighters has called for the 2021 local government elections to be put on the back-burner. The party wants them postponed to 2024. READ: EFF loses defamation appeal case against Manuel EFF leader, Julius Malema says voting will be risky, as elections can be regarded as superspreaders of COVID-19. Malema says the EFF will try to get other political parties on board about merging local and national elections in three years' time.